HEADWORD: Tanate
<hw>Ta*na"te</hw> <pr>(t⟦adot⟧*n⟦aum⟧"t⟦asl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An Asiatic wild dog (<spn>Canis
procyonoides</spn>), native of Japan and adjacent countries. It has a
short, bushy tail. Called also <altname>raccoon dog</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

